f=Product/ux/operational/commands/ux-commands.md · h1:ux — Command Triggers=\| Trigger phrases \| Skill \| Shortcut \| · h1:ux — Command Triggers=\|---\|---\|---\| · h1:ux — Command Triggers=\| "do we know", "have we researched", "find the study", "is this known", "cite research" \| research-repository \| /repo \| · h1:ux — Command Triggers=\| "run a study", "interview users", "usability test", "survey", "design the research" \| study-design \| /study \| · h1:ux — Command Triggers=\| "what does the data say", "synthesize", "findings", "how confident", "the takeaway" \| synthesis-discipline \| /synth \| · h1:ux — Command Triggers=\| "what are customers saying", "support themes", "reviews", "NPS verbatims" \| voice-of-customer-intake \| /voc \| · h2:Precedence=Any new-study request routes research-repository FIRST (query before you run); /study un-queried question bounces /repo. claim entering PRD pass synthesis-discipline's confidence flag unflagged claims bounce. Voice-of-customer patterns directional evidence, verdicts strong ones become /study GAPs, never product decisions.